tl;dr love y'all <3

At the time of posting, it has just turned 12:00 AM on June 15th, 2017, which means it is the end of the last finals week of the 2016-2017 school year! It's been a wild ride here at Stanford Memes for Edgy Trees, and I just wanted to thank everyone for their support over the past 7 months or so. Obviously, this page was started as a direct riff on the popular college meme page trend started by Berkeley, as (surprisingly) we had no meme page of our own. It's developed since then into a surprisingly positive community, where people can joke about ProFros, CS majors, and MTL without any malice; there's been nearly none of the drama or personal attacks that seem to plague other similar pages. I feel really happy every time someone posts or tells me in person that the meme page has given them a good laugh in one of the stressful moments that abound at Stanford. Ignoring the ironic hate, it seems that the group has an extremely favorable reception from people overall. My main goal with the page has been to give y'all an occasional break from the struggles of a Stanford student, and I have to thank everyone who's posted for helping to distract your peers from a sometimes overwhelming situation. Of course, there are plenty of non-Stanford students in this group as well, and hopefully the memes here have had a similar impact on you!

As we head into summer (finally), there are two likely outcomes for content in this group. It'll either slow down to winter break levels, or it'll devolve into trash 3-month old memes like the Mask Off challenge (lookin at UCBMFET here üëÄ). Hopefully we avoid either of these fates, and the students who are staying on campus can post fire memes about curing cancer or whatever y'all are doing over the summer, but if not, we will be back in full force come fall :) 

To keep this (kinda) brief, I'll skip any sentimental stuff and just thank everyone who's helped the group, either by posting or modding! shout-out to Ivan for keeping the group alive over winter break and providing us with one of our banners, as well as Elijah for being an OG and helping with a bunch of the text posts and such. Finally, huge thanks to every member who's supported the group, much love <3

P.S. if anyone's still on campus and wants to help deloft a bed tomorrow hit me up high-keyüôÉ

It is with great sadness that I am shuttering the thriving enterprise that is CardinalFights. Under undisclosed terms ($2 million dollars haha keep it v chill tho), all of our assets and employees are being sold to a major Silicon Valley player, where we will spend the rest of our days building advertising tools and sipping Soylent on a covered rooftop.

But it would be inappropriate to end this dream without a worthy paean to you, fellow Cardinal. After hundreds of fights over the past two years, my vision has entered reality. Meyer Green has turned into the paragon of bloodshed and wanton depravity that its creators always imagined. What started as a knee-jerk reaction to someone stealing my drink at Coupa has blossomed into something much bigger than a Four Berry Smoothie.

What it is, I cannot describe. Perhaps it the decades-long culmination of our collective rage at nothing, yet somehow everything. Our generation has grown up in an era of unbridled violence borne of intolerance. We reacted by punching everyone in the face, regardless of class, caste, creed, and color.

And then we kept punching them until it didn't even matter. To you, my friends, thank you for your participation.
